George Bailey
lassoes stork.

1598
01:14:31,134 --> 01:14:32,669
Lassoes a stork!

1599
01:14:34,538 --> 01:14:36,272
Well, you...

1600
01:14:36,305 --> 01:14:38,274
You mean you...

1601
01:14:38,307 --> 01:14:40,409
What is it,
a boy or a girl?

1602
01:14:40,443 --> 01:14:41,444
Mmm-hmm.

1603
01:14:43,880 --> 01:14:46,115
JOSEPH: Now, you've
probably already guessed

1604
01:14:46,149 --> 01:14:48,384
that George never
leaves Bedford Falls.

1605
01:14:48,417 --> 01:14:49,753
CLARENCE: No!

1606
01:14:49,786 --> 01:14:52,822
Mary had her baby,
a boy.

1607
01:14:52,856 --> 01:14:55,224
Then she had
another one, a girl.

1608
01:14:55,258 --> 01:14:57,293
Day after day
she worked away,

1609
01:14:57,326 --> 01:15:00,429
remaking the old
Granville house
into a home.

1610
01:15:00,463 --> 01:15:04,033
Night after night,
George came back
late from the office.

1611
01:15:07,771 --> 01:15:10,006
Potter was bearing
down hard.

1612
01:15:15,211 --> 01:15:17,614
Then came a war.

1613
01:15:17,647 --> 01:15:21,651
Ma Bailey and Mrs. Hatch
joined the Red Cross
and sewed.

1614
01:15:21,685 --> 01:15:25,989
Mary had two more babies
but still found time
to run the USO.

1615
01:15:26,022 --> 01:15:29,826
Sam Wainwright made
a fortune in plastic
hoods for planes.

1616
01:15:29,859 --> 01:15:32,295
Potter became head
of the draft board.

